The Mananchira Vellimadukunnu Road Action Committee led by historian M.G.S. Narayanan has demanded that the State government allot the entire amount required for the acquisition of land for the widening of the 8.4 km stretch of Mananchira- Vellimadukunnu road of the National Highway 766 that passes through the city.In a memorandum submitted to the Kerala Pradesh Congress Committee president V.M. Sudheeran here on Monday, the committee president Narayanan said that the road widening project should be included in as a mega project for the city.Chief Minister Oommen Chandy during his mass contact programme in Kozhikode had promised to convert the Mananchira- Vellimadukunnu road into a four-lane carriageway. The project was a long-pending dream of the people of the city, he said.Dr. Narayanan said that a sum of Rs 306 crore would be required to acquire land for the road widening project. So far the Revenue department had received only Rs 60 crore. The remaining Rs 246 crore should be allocated in the upcoming State budget, he said.Programme as scheduledMeanwhile, the committee also decided to go ahead with its proposed ‘Jana Jagratha Sadasssu’ involving the residents of the city from January 22. Kozhikode Mayor V.K.C. Mammed Koya, A. Pradeepkumar, MLA, M.K. Raghavan, MP, representatives of political parties, city corporation councillors will take part in the programme near the Public Library at Mananchira at 5 p.m., action committee general secretary M.P. Vasudevan said.